.SH NAME
ber_memalloc, ber_memcalloc, ber_memrealloc, ber_memfree \- LBER memory allocators
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.ft B
#include <lber.h>
.ft
.fi
.LP
.nf
.ft B
void * ber_memalloc(
	ber_len_t bytes )
.ft
.fi
.LP
.nf
.ft B
void * ber_memcalloc(
	ber_len_t nelems, ber_len_t bytes )
.ft
.fi
.LP
.nf
.ft B
void * ber_memrealloc(
	void \(**ptr,
	ber_len_t bytes);
.ft
.fi
.LP
.nf
.ft B
void * ber_memfree(
	void \(**ptr );
.ft
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
These routines are used to allocate/deallocate memory used/returned
by the Lightweight BER library as required by
.BR lber-encode (3)
and
.BR lber-decode (3).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lber-decode (3)
.BR lber-encode (3)
.BR lber-types (3)
.LP
